🌐 4. MiniDash Index Page Buttons (HTML + JS)

These buttons download the .txt files and rename them on download.

You can drop this directly into your MiniDash index page.

<div class="cmr-buttons">
    <button onclick="downloadScript('Structure.txt','Structure.txt')">
        Download A — Structure
    </button>

    <button onclick="downloadScript('Listener.txt','Listener.txt')">
        Download B — Listener
    </button>

    <button onclick="downloadScript('activate.txt','activate.ps1')">
        Button C — Activator
    </button>
</div>

<script>
async function downloadScript(source, targetName) {
    const response = await fetch(source);
    const text = await response.text();

    const blob = new Blob([text], { type: "text/plain" });
    const link = document.createElement("a");

    link.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    link.download = targetName;
    link.click();

    URL.revokeObjectURL(link.href);
}
</script>


✔ Button A downloads Structure.txt

✔ Button B downloads Listener.txt

✔ Button C downloads activate.ps1 (already renamed)

The user then runs activate.ps1 once, and the entire system installs itself.

